IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: TO PROVIDE FREE PREGNANCY/PARENTING SERVICES TO WOMEN AND THEIR FAMILIES FACING UNPLANNED PREGNANCIES, AND TO PROVIDE LIMITED STD TESTING AND TREATMENT.
IRS990.MissionDescription: TO PROVIDE FREE PREGNANCY/PARENTING SERVICES TO WOMEN AND THEIR FAMILIES FACING UNPLANNED PREGNANCIES, AND TO PROVIDE LIMITED STD TESTING AND TREATMENT.
IRS990.Description: MEDICAL SUPPORT SERVICES: PREGNANCY RELATED: PREGNANCY TESTING: PREGNANCY TESTS ARE ALL PHARMACEUTICAL LEVEL URINE TESTS (99% ACCURATE) AND PERFORMED BY A LICENSED NURSING PROFESSIONAL. THE TEST IS ADMINISTERED AND RESULTS GIVEN IN A TIMELY FASHION (USUALLY ABOUT 30 MINUTES FROM THE TIME OF THE MEDICAL INTAKE AND ADMINISTRATION OF THE URINE TEST.) FIRST TRIMESTER ULTRASOUND: ULTRASOUNDS ARE PERFORMED BY A LICENSED REGISTERED NURSE TRAINED IN ULTRASOUND. ULTRASOUNDS CONFIRM AN INTRAUTERINE PREGNANCY BY THREE POINTS: GESTATIONAL AGE DETERMINED BY CROWN/RUMP MEASUREMENTS, CARDIAC ACTIVITY TRACING, AND VISUALLY DETERMINING THAT THE PREGNANCY IS PLACED IN THE UTERUS. ALL ULTRASOUNDS ARE ADMINISTERED BY OUR NURSE PROFESSIONALS UNDER THE DIRECTORSHIP OF OUR VOLUNTEER MEDICAL DIRECTOR (LICENSED PRACTICING OB/GYN). SEXUAL HEALTH: LIMITED STD/STI TESTING AND TREATMENT: STD/STI TESTING FOR CHLAMYDIA AND GONORRHEA IS ADMINISTERED THROUGH A URINE TEST. THE SPECIMENS ARE TESTED AT A LOCAL LAB AND THE RESULTS ARE GIVEN AS SOON AS POSSIBLE TO THE MEDICAL STAFF AT CARE NET. IF POSITIVE A VOLUNTEER TEAM OF LICENSED DOCTORS ROTATE TREATMENT DATES AND ADMINISTER TREATMENT PRESCRIBED BY OUR MEDICAL DIRECTOR TO THE CLIENT. PROPER STATE/LOCAL FILINGS THROUGH THE HEALTH DEPARTMENT ARE COMPLETED. SEXUAL INTEGRITY EDUCATION DURING THE CLIENT'S APPOINTMENT ALLOWS A FULL ROUNDED AND EDUCATED FUTURE CHOICE TO ENSURE A HEALTHY LIFE STYLE IN RELATIONSHIPS FREE FROM THE WORRY OF DISEASES. ALL EDUCATION AND INFORMATION IS APPROVED AND OVERSEEN BY OUR MEDICAL DIRECTOR AND DELIVERED BY OUR LICENSED NURSING STAFF. IF THE CLIENT SHOULD CHOOSE TO MEET WITH A PERSONAL SUPPORT MENTOR THEY MAY TO REVIEW A CURRICULUM OF HEALTHY LIFESTYLE CHOICES AND GOALS.

Activity2.Description: EDUCATIONAL SUPPORT SERVICES: PARENTING: EARN WHILE YOU LEARN: IN 2005 THE CENTER IMPROVED THE PARENTING SUPPORT EDUCATION PROGRAM WITH THE ACQUISITION OF A QUALITY PARENTING EDUCATION CURRICULUM, EARN WHILE YOU LEARN, THROUGH GENEROUS SUPPORTERS. ALL POSITIVE PREGNANCY TESTING CLIENTS WERE OFFERED ENROLLMENT TO THIS PROGRAM ALLOWING INDIVIDUAL MENTORING SESSIONS. IN 2010, THE CENTER BEGAN OFFERING INDIVIDUAL AS WELL AS GROUP CLASS SESSIONS. THE CLIENTS ARE ABLE TO MEET WITH NURSES AND TRAINED SUPPORT MENTORS TO LEARN A WELL-ROUNDED PROGRAM INCLUDING PRE-NATAL, NUTRITION, PREPARATION OF YOUR HOME AND FAMILY, BIRTHING AND NEWBORN CARE, AS WELL AS A VARIETY OF OTHER PERTINENT SUBJECTS FOR PARENTS. EACH SESSION ALLOWS THE CLIENT TO "EARN" VOUCHERS TO REDEEM AT OUR ON-SITE BABY BOUTIQUE FOR NEW AND SLIGHTLY USED MATERNITY AND BABY ITEMS FOR THEIR GROWING FAMILY. THE CLIENTS ARE ELIGIBLE FOR THE PROGRAM UP THROUGH THE CHILD'S FIRST TWO YEARS OF LIFE. ALL MOMS AND PARTNERS ARE ELIGIBLE FOR THIS SUPPORT PROGRAM WHEN THEY OBTAIN THEIR PREGNANCY TEST AND/OR ULTRASOUND AT THE CENTER. 2011 BROUGHT THE INCREASED OUTREACH OF THE PROGRAM BY THE ACQUISITION OF THE SPANISH CURRICULUM, AGAIN RECEIVED BY GENEROUS SUPPORTERS. MAN2MAN: IN 2009 THE SPECIALIZED OUTREACH OF OUR MAN2MAN PROGRAM. THIS PROGRAM BEGAN WITH THE NATIONAL FATHERHOOD INITIATIVE (NFI) TWO YEAR GRANT RECEIVED FOR THE YEARS 2009 AND 2010. THIS PROGRAM ENCOURAGED FATHERS TO MEET IN A GROUP SETTING AND UTILIZE A NATIONAL FATHERHOOD CURRICULUM ALLOWING THEM TO LEARN HOW TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THEIR BABY. SINCE THE END OF THIS TWO YEAR GRANT THE CENTER HAS CONTINUED WITH THE FATHERHOOD PROGRAM UTILIZING DIFFERENT CURRICULUMS AND IS CURRENTLY OBTAINING UPDATED NFI CURRICULUM. TEEN MOMS: A TEEN MOMS PROGRAM MEETS ONE TIME PER MONTH. IN THIS GROUP SESSION MOMS FROM UP TO 20 YEARS OF AGE ARE AUTOMATICALLY ELIGIBLE. GROUP SESSIONS ALLOW THE MOMS TO HAVE CAMARADERIE WITH EACH OTHER AND DEVELOP A NETWORK OF FRIENDSHIPS AND SUPPORT OUTSIDE OF THE CENTER. THE GROUP LEARNS THROUGH A VIDEOS AND PROJECT CENTERED EDUCATION. PACE (POST ABORTION CARE AND EDUCATION): PACE IS A SAFE HAVEN FOR A GROUP OF WOMEN WHO HAVE EXPERIENCED AN ABORTION IN THEIR PAST. THIS IS A 13 WEEK BIBLE STUDY EXPLORING FORGIVENESS AND RESTORATION THROUGH THE HEALING TIME IN SCRIPTURE AND WITH EACH OTHER. CLIENTS ARE OFFERED THIS PROGRAM WHEN THEY HAVE SHARED A PAST ABORTION IN THEIR MEDICAL INTAKE/TESTING APPOINTMENT.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: ORGANIZATION'S PROCESS USED TO REVIEW FORM 990
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS THE 990 AND APPROVES IT PRIOR TO BEING FILED WITH THE IRS
THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVISES POLICIES AND PROCEDURES INCLUDING CONFLICT OF INTEREST ON AN ANNUAL BASIS.
COMPENSATION OF KEY EMPLOYEES IS DETERMINED BASED ON A NATIONAL SURVEY OF SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS.
THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
